{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents the Spire (Spir) family, including vertebrate Spire-1 and Spire-2, Ciona savignyi PEM-5 and Drosophila dSpire. They contain a KIND (kinase noncatalytic C-lobe) domain and four actin-binding WH2 (WASP homology 2) domains [[cite:PUB00018535]]. They act as actin nucleation factors [[cite:PUB00071257]] and are involved in a novel actin-dependent mechanism for long range vesicle transport [[cite:PUB00071259]]. Although Spire proteins are capable of nucleating actin polymerisation in vitro by themselves, they have been found to act in cooperation with members of another family of actin nucleators: the formin subgroup (FMN) of formins [[cite:PUB00072489]]. Spire/formin cooperation is considered to have a major regulatory function in mammalian oocyte maturation [[cite:PUB00072490]]. The structure of Spire has been revealed [[cite:PUB00055242], [cite:PUB00071258]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2yle", "name" "Crystal structure of the human Spir-1 KIND FSI domain in complex with the FSI peptide"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR21345" "SPIRE"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Protein Spire", "short" "Spire"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 884, "taxa" 3556, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 4609, "sets" 0, "proteins" 4609, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2938}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR029901", :literature {"PUB00055242" {"URL" nil, "issue" "26", "authors" ["Ducka AM" "Joel P" "Popowicz GM" "Trybus KM" "Schleicher M" "Noegel AA" "Huber R" "Holak TA" "Sitar T."], "ISO_journal" "Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1005347107", "medline_journal" "Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A", "title" "Structures of actin-